               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350511-name-171" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-171" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-171" type="surname" value="FELTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-171" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>Charles Felton</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a constable of St. Thomas the Apostle. On Saturday afternoon, the 18th of April, I saw the prisoner take a coat out of a chaise which stood opposite No. 32, Bucklersbury—he put it under his coat, and ran away with it—I followed him, and he threw it down—I called "Stop thief." and a gentleman collared him—I never lost sight of him—I gave him in custody to a policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
